data <- read.csv("CleanedDataset.csv")

Analysis of founded year

data %>% count(founded_year)%>% arrange(-n) %>% head(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(reorder(founded_year, n), n)) + geom_col(aes(fill=founded_year)) + coord_flip() +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  ggtitle("Year Founded") + xlab("Year") + ylab("Count")

Top 10 market leaders

data %>%  
  filter(market != "" & funding_total_usd) %>%
  group_by(market) %>%
  summarise(total_funding = sum(funding_total_usd) / 1000000) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_funding)) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = market, y = total_funding)) + geom_col(aes(fill = market)) + 
  theme(axis.text.x=element_blank()) +
  ggtitle("Top 10 Markets with maximum fundings") + xlab("Markets") + ylab("Total Fundings in millions")

Country wise analysis

data %>%  
  filter(country_code != "" & funding_total_usd) %>%
  group_by(country_code) %>%
  summarise(total_funding = sum(funding_total_usd) / 1000000000) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_funding)) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = country_code, y = total_funding)) + geom_col(aes(fill = country_code)) + coord_flip() +
  ggtitle("Top 10 Countries with maximum fundings") + xlab("Countries") + ylab("Total Fundings in billions")

Top 10 states of USA with maximum funding

data %>%
  filter(country_code == 'USA' & state_code != '') %>%
  group_by(state_code) %>%
  summarise(total_funding = sum(funding_total_usd) / 1000000000) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_funding)) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = state_code, y = total_funding)) + geom_col(aes(fill = state_code)) +
  ggtitle("Top 10 States in USA with maximum fudings") + xlab("States") + ylab("Total fundings in millions")

Top markets of operating companies

data %>%
  filter(status == 'operating' & market != '') %>%
  group_by(market) %>%
  summarise(total_funding = sum(funding_total_usd) / 1000000000) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_funding)) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = market, y = total_funding)) + geom_col(aes(fill = market)) +
  ggtitle("Top 10 markets of operating startups") + xlab("Markets") + ylab("Total fundings in millions")

Considering analysis only for the top 5 markets since the dataset is too large for processing

data$market <- as.character(data$market)
data <- data[data$market == ' Biotechnology ' | data$market == ' Mobile ' | data$market == ' Software ' | data$market == ' Clean Technology ' | data$market == ' Health Care ',]
nrow(data)
## [1] 12698

Converting market colum to numeric

data$market[data$market == ' Software '] <- '1'
data$market[data$market == ' Biotechnology '] <- '2'
data$market[data$market == ' Mobile '] <- '3'
data$market[data$market == ' Clean Technology '] <- '4'
data$market[data$market == ' Health Care '] <- '5'

data$market <- as.numeric(data$market)

Converting status column to numeric

data$status <- as.character(data$status)
data$status[data$status == 'acquired'] <- '1'
data$status[data$status == 'operating'] <- '2'
data$status[data$status == 'closed'] <- '3'

data$status <- as.numeric(data$status)

# replacing NA's with the median value
data$status <- replace(data$status, is.na(data$status), median(data$status, na.rm = TRUE))

further reducing variables

data$roundtotal = data$round_A + data$round_B + data$round_C+ data$round_D+ data$round_E+ data$round_F+ data$round_G
data <- subset(data, select = -c(round_A, round_B, round_C, round_D, round_E, round_F, round_G))

writing the Processed Data as a csv file

write.csv(data, "ProcessedData.csv", row.names = FALSE)
